trend_summary: Across the series, built-up area edges creep outward, vacant parcels infill with housing, and commercial strips thicken along the north–south highway. Some older industrial parcels convert to retail or mixed use, while parks and tree canopy expand slightly, retaining a medium-density, suburban character overall.
notable_changes: North–south arterial widened and lined with new commercial/warehouse buildings.
Several vacant residential lots in the southeast and center filled with single-family roofs.
Industrial buildings near the northern rail corridor replaced by big-box retail pads.
West-side athletic complex upgraded with a new oval track and larger stands.
Tree canopy and landscaped green space increase, especially in the east and southwest.
